modules.description: Provides functions to initialize, update, and validate estimates based on input data, including parsing raw values and applying constraints. Works with the `estimate` type, which includes fields for target values, confidence levels, and adjustment factors. Used to generate reliable forecasts in financial modeling and resource allocation scenarios.

Provides functions for measuring execution time of code snippets, including start and stop timers and duration calculation. Operates on integers to represent time intervals in nanoseconds. Used to profile specific code sections during performance testing.

Calculates and refines estimates using input data, incorporating target values, confidence levels, and adjustment factors. Supports parsing, validation, and iterative updates to ensure accuracy in forecasting. Operations include initializing estimates, applying constraints, and generating forecasts. Can be used to model financial scenarios, optimize resource allocation, and track performance metrics over time.
